  "text": "For each torque generator, the properties of muscle and tendon were modelled using a rotational muscle-tendon complex comprising a contractile element and a series elastic element. The torque T exerted at a joint was calculated as the product of the activation level a t and the maximum voluntary torque defined by a nineparameter function of contractile element angle and angular velocity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Specifically a six parameter function f(o) was used to describe the torque-angular velocity relationship multiplied by the isometric torque parameter T iso [CITATION_3] ) and a two-parameter quadratic function f(y) for the torque-angle relationship [CITATION_4] as follows:",
